# Smart HR Client — Full UI/UX Redesign

This document outlines the planned approach for redesigning the client application's UI/UX without altering any existing APIs or routing logic. The redesign focuses on implementing a modern styling system, adding multi-theme and accent color support, and creating a more professional layout.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Design System Upgrade (Tokens, Themes, Accent)

Extending the CSS variable system using standard HSL values (to ensure full compatibility with Tailwind `hsl(var(...))` mapping).

#### [MODIFY] [index.css](file:///d:/%D9%85%D8%B4%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B9/14-2-2026/2026-2-13/smart_performance_system/client/src/index.css)
- Clean up duplicate OKLCH definition blocks and standardize the entire file to use `hsl` and `rem`.
- Migrate `.dark` to `[data-theme="dark"]`.
- Add `[data-theme="midnight"]` with a deep blue/indigo theme pattern.
- Add `[data-theme="sand"]` with a warm light theme pattern.
- Update `[data-accent="..."]` overrides to specifically target `--primary`, `--ring`, and relevant branding tokens.

#### [MODIFY] [tailwind.config.cjs](file:///d:/%D9%85%D8%B4%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B9/14-2-2026/2026-2-13/smart_performance_system/client/tailwind.config.cjs)
- Remove `darkMode: ["class"]` to support the data-theme approach natively if needed, or update the selector configuration.

#### [MODIFY] [AppearanceContext.tsx](file:///d:/%D9%85%D8%B4%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B9/14-2-2026/2026-2-13/smart_performance_system/client/src/contexts/AppearanceContext.tsx)
- Expand `ThemeType` to include `midnight` and `sand`.
- Refactor the context to toggle `data-theme` on the HTML root element instead of adding/removing classes, streamlining theme switching.

